Considering that there are 18 days to complete this translation before the
deadline, this makes more than 9,000 words per day (if we include a
conversion factor). I doubt any single translator working alone would be
able to deliver the entire translation for this deadline. This means that
they will certainly need to divide up the translation among multiple
translators in any case, if they wish to meet the deadline.

If you do still want to work on this job and perhaps get some experience,
instead of simply declining, you might suggest that you could take a piece
of the job. I would recommend taking an extremely small piece so that you
would have more than enough time to do it, considering your inexperience. If
you finish your bit early, they might send you more. Hopefully, the client
will provide feedback in this arrangement and you can improve your craft.

The client may simply not want to be bothered by dealing with you, and if
so, keep looking for something else.

Frankly, I don't know anything about the test you took or whether or not you
are qualified to take on professional translation. But you did say that you
have done some translation on the side. If you have received positive
feedback on the work you have done so far, by all means continue if you
wish.

But certainly be cautious that you do not overextend yourself.

Regards,

